    <meta charset="utf-8">

  </head>
  <body>
    <h1>Build Pick Order</h1>
    <h2>Basic Path</h2>
    <ol>
      <li><p>The software begins when the Inventory Manager
	  selects "Pick Order Managerment".</p></li>
      <li><p>The Inventory Manager selects "Build Pick Order".</p></li>
      <li><p>The software checks that two stockrooms are being used.</p></li>
      <li><p>The software prompts for the Inventory Manager for
	  the department groups to show or departments to show. </p></li>
      <li><p>The Inventory Manager enters the departments and department groups to show.</p></li>
      <li><p>For each department</p></li>
      <ol>
	<li><p>The software finds products with the department.</p></li>
	<li><p>The software finds the quantity on hand of the product
	    in the secondary stockroom.</p></li>
	<li><p>The software finds the quantity on hand of the product
	    in the primary stockroom.</p></li>
	<li><p>The software retrieves the secondary par of the product.</p></li>
	<li><p>If there is no secondary par, the default is one box. </p></li>

	<li><p>The software determines an order quantity by ordering upto the secondary
	    par.</p></li>
	<li><p>If the order quantity is greater than the quantity on hand within the
	    primary stockroom, the order quantity is reduced so that the order
	    is possible.</p></li>
	<li><p>The software adds the product and ordered quantity to the pick order.</p></li>
      </ol>

      <li><p>The software enters the pick order under today's date.</p></li>
      <li><p>The software shows the pick order to the Inventory Manager. The default
	  order is alphabetical, by department then description, but the order may be sorted
	  by department then quantity ordered. The software prompts the Inventory
          Manager for the shipped quantities. </p></li>
      <li><p>The software allows the Inventory Manager to print the pick order such
	     that it may be filled.</p></li>
      <li><p>The Inventory Manager fills out the shipped quantities.</p></li>
      <li><p>The software highlights any descrepencies.</p></li>
      <li><p>The software prompts the Inventory Manager to OK the pick order. </p></li>
      <li><p>The Inventory Manager agrees.</p></li>
      <li><p>The software creates a new transfer using the specific pick order.</p></li>
    <h2>Alternate Paths</h2>
    <h3>DB Error</h3>
  </body>

</html>
